==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wolframite
<hw>Wol"fram*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.,
<ets>wolframit</ets>, <ets>wolfram</ets>; <ets>wolf</ets> wolf +
<ets>rahm</ets> cream, soot; cf. G. <ets>wolfsruss</ets> wolfram, lit.,
wolf's soot.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Tungstate of iron and
manganese, generally of a brownish or grayish black color, submetallic
luster, and high specific gravity. It occurs in cleavable masses, and
also crystallized. Called also <altname>wolfram</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wolframium</ent>⟦br⟧
